'''Bengt Andersson''' (born March 6, 1966 in Mora, Sweden) is a [[Sweden|Swedish]] rifle shooter. He was a [[300 metre rifle|300 m rifle]] specialist during most of the 1990s and won an individual gold medal in [[300 metre rifle prone]] and was a part of the winning team at the 1998 [[ISSF World Shooting Championships]] in [[Zaragoza]], [[Spain]].
